===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|fesaunt}}, {{m|enm|fesant}}, from {{der|en|fro|fesan}}, from {{der|en|la|phāsiānus}}, from {{der|en|grc|φᾱσιανός}}, meaning “[bird] of the river {{m|grc|Φᾶσις}}”, from where, it was supposed, the bird spread to the west. Replaced native {{der|en|ang|wōrhana}}, a variant of  {{m|ang|mōrhana}}. More at [[moorhen]].

